==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Potentate
<hw>Po"ten*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>potentatus</ets>, fr. <ets>potentare</ets> to exercise power: cf.
F. <ets>potentat</ets>. See <er>Potent</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>One who is potent; one who possesses great power or sway; a prince,
sovereign, or monarch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The blessed and only <qex>potentate</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim. vi.
15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cherub and seraph, <qex>potentates</qex> and thrones.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Potential</ent>⟦br⟧
